26 // half
27 // slot Frame
28 // -----+--------------------+---------------------------
29 // n+3 | parameter n |
30 // ... | ... |
31 // 4 | parameter 1 | or parameter 2
32 // 3 | parameter 0 | or parameter 1
33 // 2 | (result address) | or parameter 0
34 // -----+--------------------+---------------------------
35 // 1 | return addr (lr) |
36 // 0 | previous frame (fp)|
37 // -----+--------------------+ <-- frame ptr (fp)
38 // -1 | StackFrame::WASM |
39 // -2 | instance |
40 // -3 | feedback vector |
41 // -4 | tiering budget |
42 // -----+--------------------+---------------------------
43 // -5 | slot 0 (high) | ^
44 // -6 | slot 0 (low) | |
45 // -7 | slot 1 (high) | Frame slots
46 // -8 | slot 1 (low) | |
47 // | | v
48 // -----+--------------------+ <-- stack ptr (sp)
49 //
50 static_assert(2 * kSystemPointerSize == LiftoffAssembler::kStackSlotSize,
51  "Slot size should be twice the size of the 32 bit pointer.");
52 // kPatchInstructionsRequired sets a maximum limit of how many instructions that
53 // PatchPrepareStackFrame will use in order to increase the stack appropriately.
54 // Three instructions are required to sub a large constant, movw + movt + sub.
55 constexpr int32_t kPatchInstructionsRequired = 3;
56 constexpr int kHalfStackSlotSize = LiftoffAssembler::kStackSlotSize >> 1;
57 
58 inline MemOperand GetStackSlot(int offset) { return MemOperand(fp, -offset); }
59 
60 inline MemOperand GetHalfStackSlot(int offset, RegPairHalf half) {
61  int32_t half_offset =
62  half == kLowWord ? 0 : LiftoffAssembler::kStackSlotSize / 2;
63  return MemOperand(offset > 0 ? fp : sp, -offset + half_offset);
64 }

66 inline MemOperand GetInstanceDataOperand() {
67  return GetStackSlot(WasmLiftoffFrameConstants::kInstanceDataOffset);
68 }

70 inline MemOperand GetMemOp(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
71  UseScratchRegisterScope* temps, Register addr,
72  Register offset, int32_t offset_imm,
73  unsigned shift_amount = 0) {
74  if (offset != no_reg) {
75  if (offset_imm == 0) return MemOperand(addr, offset, LSL, shift_amount);
76  Register tmp = temps->Acquire();
77  if (shift_amount == 0) {
78  assm->add(tmp, offset, Operand(offset_imm));
79  } else {
80  assm->lsl(tmp, offset, Operand(shift_amount));
81  assm->add(tmp, tmp, Operand(offset_imm));
82  }
83  return MemOperand(addr, tmp);
84  }
85  return MemOperand(addr, offset_imm);
86 }
87 
88 inline Register CalculateActualAddress(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
89  UseScratchRegisterScope* temps,
90  Register addr_reg, Register offset_reg,
91  uintptr_t offset_imm,
92  Register result_reg = no_reg) {
93  if (offset_reg == no_reg && offset_imm == 0) {
94  if (result_reg == addr_reg || result_reg == no_reg) return addr_reg;
95  assm->mov(result_reg, addr_reg);
96  return result_reg;
97  }
98  if (result_reg == no_reg) result_reg = temps->Acquire();
99  if (offset_reg == no_reg) {
100  assm->add(result_reg, addr_reg, Operand(offset_imm));
101  } else {
102  assm->add(result_reg, addr_reg, Operand(offset_reg));
103  if (offset_imm != 0) assm->add(result_reg, result_reg, Operand(offset_imm));
104  }
105  return result_reg;
106 }

108 inline Condition MakeUnsigned(Condition cond) {
109  switch (cond) {
110  case kLessThan:
111  return kUnsignedLessThan;
112  case kLessThanEqual:
113  return kUnsignedLessThanEqual;
114  case kGreaterThan:
115  return kUnsignedGreaterThan;
116  case kGreaterThanEqual:
117  return kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual;
118  case kEqual:
119  case kNotEqual:
120  case kUnsignedLessThan:
121  case kUnsignedLessThanEqual:
122  case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
123  case kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual:
124  return cond;
125  default:
126  UNREACHABLE();
127  }
128 }

130 template <void (Assembler::*op)(Register, Register, Register, SBit, Condition),
131  void (Assembler::*op_with_carry)(Register, Register, const Operand&,
132  SBit, Condition)>
133 inline void I64Binop(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
134  LiftoffRegister lhs, LiftoffRegister rhs) {
135  Register dst_low = dst.low_gp();
136  if (dst_low == lhs.high_gp() || dst_low == rhs.high_gp()) {
137  dst_low =
138  assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, LiftoffRegList{lhs, rhs, dst.high_gp()})
139  .gp();
140  }
141  (assm->*op)(dst_low, lhs.low_gp(), rhs.low_gp(), SetCC, al);
142  (assm->*op_with_carry)(dst.high_gp(), lhs.high_gp(), Operand(rhs.high_gp()),
143  LeaveCC, al);
144  if (dst_low != dst.low_gp()) assm->mov(dst.low_gp(), dst_low);
145 }
146 
147 template <void (Assembler::*op)(Register, Register, const Operand&, SBit,
148  Condition),
149  void (Assembler::*op_with_carry)(Register, Register, const Operand&,
150  SBit, Condition)>
151 inline void I64BinopI(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
152  LiftoffRegister lhs, int64_t imm) {
153  // The compiler allocated registers such that either {dst == lhs} or there is
154  // no overlap between the two.
155  DCHECK_NE(dst.low_gp(), lhs.high_gp());
156  int32_t imm_low_word = static_cast<int32_t>(imm);
157  int32_t imm_high_word = static_cast<int32_t>(imm >> 32);
158  (assm->*op)(dst.low_gp(), lhs.low_gp(), Operand(imm_low_word), SetCC, al);
159  (assm->*op_with_carry)(dst.high_gp(), lhs.high_gp(), Operand(imm_high_word),
160  LeaveCC, al);
161 }
162 
163 template <void (MacroAssembler::*op)(Register, Register, Register, Register,
164  Register),
165  bool is_left_shift>
166 inline void I64Shiftop(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
167  LiftoffRegister src, Register amount) {
168  Register src_low = src.low_gp();
169  Register src_high = src.high_gp();
170  Register dst_low = dst.low_gp();
171  Register dst_high = dst.high_gp();
172  // Left shift writes {dst_high} then {dst_low}, right shifts write {dst_low}
173  // then {dst_high}.
174  Register clobbered_dst_reg = is_left_shift ? dst_high : dst_low;
175  LiftoffRegList pinned{clobbered_dst_reg, src};
176  Register amount_capped =
177  pinned.set(assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
178  assm->and_(amount_capped, amount, Operand(0x3F));
179 
180  // Ensure that writing the first half of {dst} does not overwrite the still
181  // needed half of {src}.
182  Register* later_src_reg = is_left_shift ? &src_low : &src_high;
183  if (*later_src_reg == clobbered_dst_reg) {
184  *later_src_reg = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
185  assm->MacroAssembler::Move(*later_src_reg, clobbered_dst_reg);
186  }
187 
188  (assm->*op)(dst_low, dst_high, src_low, src_high, amount_capped);
189 }

204 enum class MinOrMax : uint8_t { kMin, kMax };
205 template <typename RegisterType>
206 inline void EmitFloatMinOrMax(LiftoffAssembler* assm, RegisterType dst,
207  RegisterType lhs, RegisterType rhs,
208  MinOrMax min_or_max) {
209  DCHECK(RegisterType::kSizeInBytes == 4 || RegisterType::kSizeInBytes == 8);
210  if (lhs == rhs) {
211  assm->MacroAssembler::Move(dst, lhs);
212  return;
213  }
214  Label done, is_nan;
215  if (min_or_max == MinOrMax::kMin) {
216  assm->MacroAssembler::FloatMin(dst, lhs, rhs, &is_nan);
217  } else {
218  assm->MacroAssembler::FloatMax(dst, lhs, rhs, &is_nan);
219  }
220  assm->b(&done);
221  assm->bind(&is_nan);
222  // Create a NaN output.
223  assm->vadd(dst, lhs, rhs);
224  assm->bind(&done);
225 }

227 inline Register EnsureNoAlias(Assembler* assm, Register reg,
228  Register must_not_alias,
229  UseScratchRegisterScope* temps) {
230  if (reg != must_not_alias) return reg;
231  Register tmp = temps->Acquire();
232  DCHECK_NE(reg, tmp);
233  assm->mov(tmp, reg);
234  return tmp;
235 }

237 inline void S128NarrowOp(LiftoffAssembler* assm, NeonDataType dt,
238  NeonDataType sdt, LiftoffRegister dst,
239  LiftoffRegister lhs, LiftoffRegister rhs) {
240  if (dst == lhs) {
241  assm->vqmovn(dt, sdt, dst.low_fp(), liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs));
242  assm->vqmovn(dt, sdt, dst.high_fp(), liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs));
243  } else {
244  assm->vqmovn(dt, sdt, dst.high_fp(), liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs));
245  assm->vqmovn(dt, sdt, dst.low_fp(), liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs));
246  }
247 }

249 inline void F64x2Compare(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
250  LiftoffRegister lhs, LiftoffRegister rhs,
251  Condition cond) {
252  DCHECK(cond == eq || cond == ne || cond == lt || cond == le);
253 
254  QwNeonRegister dest = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
255  QwNeonRegister left = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs);
256  QwNeonRegister right = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs);
257  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
258  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
259 
260  assm->mov(scratch, Operand(0));
261  assm->VFPCompareAndSetFlags(left.low(), right.low());
262  assm->mov(scratch, Operand(-1), LeaveCC, cond);
263  if (cond == lt || cond == le) {
264  // Check for NaN.
265  assm->mov(scratch, Operand(0), LeaveCC, vs);
266  }
267  assm->vmov(dest.low(), scratch, scratch);
268 
269  assm->mov(scratch, Operand(0));
270  assm->VFPCompareAndSetFlags(left.high(), right.high());
271  assm->mov(scratch, Operand(-1), LeaveCC, cond);
272  if (cond == lt || cond == le) {
273  // Check for NaN.
274  assm->mov(scratch, Operand(0), LeaveCC, vs);
275  }
276  assm->vmov(dest.high(), scratch, scratch);
277 }

279 inline void Store(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister src, MemOperand dst,
280  ValueKind kind) {
281 #ifdef DEBUG
282  // The {str} instruction needs a temp register when the immediate in the
283  // provided MemOperand does not fit into 12 bits. This happens for large stack
284  // frames. This DCHECK checks that the temp register is available when needed.
285  DCHECK(UseScratchRegisterScope{assm}.CanAcquire());
286 #endif
287  switch (kind) {
288  case kI16:
289  assm->strh(src.gp(), dst);
290  break;
291  case kI32:
292  case kRefNull:
293  case kRef:
294  assm->str(src.gp(), dst);
295  break;
296  case kI64:
297  // Positive offsets should be lowered to kI32.
298  assm->str(src.low_gp(), MemOperand(dst.rn(), dst.offset()));
299  assm->str(
300  src.high_gp(),
301  MemOperand(dst.rn(), dst.offset() + liftoff::kHalfStackSlotSize));
302  break;
303  case kF32:
304  assm->vstr(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp()), dst);
305  break;
306  case kF64:
307  assm->vstr(src.fp(), dst);
308  break;
309  case kS128: {
310  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
311  Register addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(assm, &temps, dst.rn(),
312  no_reg, dst.offset());
313  assm->vst1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(src.low_fp(), 2), NeonMemOperand(addr));
314  break;
315  }
316  default:
317  UNREACHABLE();
318  }
319 }
320 
321 inline void Load(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst, MemOperand src,
322  ValueKind kind) {
323  switch (kind) {
324  case kI16:
325  assm->ldrh(dst.gp(), src);
326  break;
327  case kI32:
328  case kRefNull:
329  case kRef:
330  assm->ldr(dst.gp(), src);
331  break;
332  case kI64:
333  assm->ldr(dst.low_gp(), MemOperand(src.rn(), src.offset()));
334  assm->ldr(
335  dst.high_gp(),
336  MemOperand(src.rn(), src.offset() + liftoff::kHalfStackSlotSize));
337  break;
338  case kF32:
339  assm->vldr(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()), src);
340  break;
341  case kF64:
342  assm->vldr(dst.fp(), src);
343  break;
344  case kS128: {
345  // Get memory address of slot to fill from.
346  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
347  Register addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(assm, &temps, src.rn(),
348  no_reg, src.offset());
349  assm->vld1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp(), 2), NeonMemOperand(addr));
350  break;
351  }
352  default:
353  UNREACHABLE();
354  }
355 }

357 constexpr int MaskFromNeonDataType(NeonDataType dt) {
358  switch (dt) {
359  case NeonS8:
360  case NeonU8:
361  return 7;
362  case NeonS16:
363  case NeonU16:
364  return 15;
365  case NeonS32:
366  case NeonU32:
367  return 31;
368  case NeonS64:
369  case NeonU64:
370  return 63;
371  default:
372  UNREACHABLE();
373  return 0;
374  }
375 }
376 
377 enum ShiftDirection { kLeft, kRight };
378 
379 template <ShiftDirection dir = kLeft, NeonDataType dt, NeonSize sz>
380 inline void EmitSimdShift(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
381  LiftoffRegister lhs, LiftoffRegister rhs) {
382  constexpr int mask = MaskFromNeonDataType(dt);
383  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
384  QwNeonRegister tmp = temps.AcquireQ();
385  Register shift = temps.Acquire();
386  assm->and_(shift, rhs.gp(), Operand(mask));
387  assm->vdup(sz, tmp, shift);
388  if (dir == kRight) {
389  assm->vneg(sz, tmp, tmp);
390  }
391  assm->vshl(dt, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst),
392  liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs), tmp);
393 }
394 
395 template <ShiftDirection dir, NeonDataType dt>
396 inline void EmitSimdShiftImmediate(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
397  LiftoffRegister lhs, int32_t rhs) {
398  // vshr by 0 is not allowed, so check for it, and only move if dst != lhs.
399  int32_t shift = rhs & MaskFromNeonDataType(dt);
400  if (shift) {
401  if (dir == kLeft) {
402  assm->vshl(dt, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst),
403  liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs), shift);
404  } else {
405  assm->vshr(dt, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst),
406  liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs), shift);
407  }
408  } else if (dst != lhs) {
409  assm->vmov(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst),
410  liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs));
411  }
412 }
413 
414 inline void EmitAnyTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
415  LiftoffRegister src) {
416  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
417  DwVfpRegister scratch = temps.AcquireD();
418  assm->vpmax(NeonU32, scratch, src.low_fp(), src.high_fp());
419  assm->vpmax(NeonU32, scratch, scratch, scratch);
420  assm->ExtractLane(dst.gp(), scratch, NeonS32, 0);
421  assm->cmp(dst.gp(), Operand(0));
422  assm->mov(dst.gp(), Operand(1), LeaveCC, ne);
423 }

425 class CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters {
426  public:
427  explicit CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
428  LiftoffRegList pinned = {})
429  : assm_(assm), pinned_(pinned) {}
430 
431  ~CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters() {
432  for (Register reg : must_pop_) {
433  assm_->Pop(reg);
434  }
435  }
436 
437  Register Acquire() {
438  if (assm_->cache_state()->has_unused_register(kGpReg, pinned_)) {
439  return pinned_.set(
440  assm_->cache_state()->unused_register(kGpReg, pinned_).gp());
441  }
442 
443  RegList available =
444  kLiftoffAssemblerGpCacheRegs - pinned_.GetGpList() - must_pop_;
445  DCHECK(!available.is_empty());
446  // Use {last()} here so we can just iterate forwards in the destructor.
447  Register reg = available.last();
448  assm_->Push(reg);
449  must_pop_.set(reg);
450  return reg;
451  }
452 
453  private:
454  LiftoffAssembler* const assm_;
455  LiftoffRegList pinned_;
456  RegList must_pop_;
457 };

461 int LiftoffAssembler::PrepareStackFrame() {
462  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ARMv7)) {
463  bailout(kUnsupportedArchitecture, "Liftoff needs ARMv7");
464  return 0;
465  }
466  uint32_t offset = static_cast<uint32_t>(pc_offset());
467  // PatchPrepareStackFrame will patch this in order to increase the stack
468  // appropriately. Additional nops are required as the bytes operand might
469  // require extra moves to encode.
470  for (int i = 0; i < liftoff::kPatchInstructionsRequired; i++) {
471  nop();
472  }
473  DCHECK_EQ(offset + liftoff::kPatchInstructionsRequired * kInstrSize,
474  pc_offset());
475  return offset;
476 }
477 
478 void LiftoffAssembler::CallFrameSetupStub(int declared_function_index) {
479 // The standard library used by gcc tryjobs does not consider `std::find` to be
480 // `constexpr`, so wrap it in a `#ifdef __clang__` block.
481 #ifdef __clang__
482  static_assert(std::find(std::begin(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
483  std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
484  kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg) ==
485  std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters));
486 #endif
487 
488  // On ARM, we must push at least {lr} before calling the stub, otherwise
489  // it would get clobbered with no possibility to recover it.
490  Register scratch = r7;
491  mov(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM)));
492  PushCommonFrame(scratch);
493  LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister(kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg),
494  WasmValue(declared_function_index));
495  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmLiftoffFrameSetup);
496 }
497 
498 void LiftoffAssembler::PrepareTailCall(int num_callee_stack_params,
499  int stack_param_delta) {
500  {
501  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
502  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
503 
504  // Push the return address and frame pointer to complete the stack frame.
505  sub(sp, sp, Operand(8));
506  ldr(scratch, MemOperand(fp, 4));
507  str(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 4));
508  ldr(scratch, MemOperand(fp, 0));
509  str(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 0));
510 
511  // Shift the whole frame upwards.
512  int slot_count = num_callee_stack_params + 2;
513  for (int i = slot_count - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
514  ldr(scratch, MemOperand(sp, i * 4));
515  str(scratch, MemOperand(fp, (i - stack_param_delta) * 4));
516  }
517  }
518 
519  // Set the new stack and frame pointer.
520  sub(sp, fp, Operand(stack_param_delta * 4));
521  Pop(lr, fp);
522 }
523 
524 void LiftoffAssembler::AlignFrameSize() {}
525 
526 void LiftoffAssembler::PatchPrepareStackFrame(
527  int offset, SafepointTableBuilder* safepoint_table_builder,
528  bool feedback_vector_slot, size_t stack_param_slots) {
529  // The frame_size includes the frame marker and the instance slot. Both are
530  // pushed as part of frame construction, so we don't need to allocate memory
531  // for them anymore.
532  int frame_size = GetTotalFrameSize() - 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
533  // The frame setup builtin also pushes the feedback vector.
534  if (feedback_vector_slot) {
535  frame_size -= kSystemPointerSize;
536  }
537 
538  PatchingAssembler patching_assembler(AssemblerOptions{},
539  buffer_start_ + offset,
540  liftoff::kPatchInstructionsRequired);
541  if (V8_LIKELY(frame_size < 4 * KB)) {
542  // This is the standard case for small frames: just subtract from SP and be
543  // done with it.
544  patching_assembler.sub(sp, sp, Operand(frame_size));
545  patching_assembler.PadWithNops();
546  return;
547  }
548 
549  // The frame size is bigger than 4KB, so we might overflow the available stack
550  // space if we first allocate the frame and then do the stack check (we will
551  // need some remaining stack space for throwing the exception). That's why we
552  // check the available stack space before we allocate the frame. To do this we
553  // replace the {__ sub(sp, sp, framesize)} with a jump to OOL code that does
554  // this "extended stack check".
555  //
556  // The OOL code can simply be generated here with the normal assembler,
557  // because all other code generation, including OOL code, has already finished
558  // when {PatchPrepareStackFrame} is called. The function prologue then jumps
559  // to the current {pc_offset()} to execute the OOL code for allocating the
560  // large frame.
561 
562  // Emit the unconditional branch in the function prologue (from {offset} to
563  // {pc_offset()}).
564  patching_assembler.b(pc_offset() - offset - Instruction::kPcLoadDelta);
565  patching_assembler.PadWithNops();
566 
567  // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
568  // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
569  // check in the condition code.
570  RecordComment("OOL: stack check for large frame");
571  Label continuation;
572  if (frame_size < v8_flags.stack_size * 1024) {
573  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
574  Register stack_limit = temps.Acquire();
575  LoadStackLimit(stack_limit, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
576  add(stack_limit, stack_limit, Operand(frame_size));
577  cmp(sp, stack_limit);
578  b(cs /* higher or same */, &continuation);
579  }
580 
581  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
582  LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
583  regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister());
584  regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister());
585  for (auto reg : kGpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
586  for (auto reg : kFpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
587  PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
588  mov(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister(), Operand(frame_size));
589  add(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister(), fp,
590  Operand(stack_param_slots * kSystemPointerSize +
591  CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp));
592  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmHandleStackOverflow);
593  safepoint_table_builder->DefineSafepoint(this);
594  PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
595  } else {
596  Call(static_cast<Address>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
597  RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
598  // The call will not return; just define an empty safepoint.
599  safepoint_table_builder->DefineSafepoint(this);
600  if (v8_flags.debug_code) stop();
601  }
602 
603  bind(&continuation);
604 
605  // Now allocate the stack space. Note that this might do more than just
606  // decrementing the SP; consult {MacroAssembler::AllocateStackSpace}.
607  AllocateStackSpace(frame_size);
608 
609  // Jump back to the start of the function, from {pc_offset()} to
610  // right after the reserved space for the {__ sub(sp, sp, framesize)} (which
611  // is a branch now).
612  int func_start_offset =
613  offset + liftoff::kPatchInstructionsRequired * kInstrSize;
614  b(func_start_offset - pc_offset() - Instruction::kPcLoadDelta);
615 }

639 void LiftoffAssembler::CheckTierUp(int declared_func_index, int budget_used,
640  Label* ool_label,
641  const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
642  {
643  liftoff::CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters temps{this};
644  Register budget_array = temps.Acquire();
645 
646  Register instance_data = cache_state_.cached_instance_data;
647  if (instance_data == no_reg) {
648  instance_data = budget_array; // Reuse the temp register.
649  LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(instance_data);
650  }
651 
652  constexpr int kArrayOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
653  WasmTrustedInstanceData::kTieringBudgetArrayOffset);
654  ldr(budget_array, MemOperand{instance_data, kArrayOffset});
655 
656  int budget_arr_offset = kInt32Size * declared_func_index;
657  // If the offset cannot be used in the operand directly, add it once to the
658  // budget array to avoid doing this multiple times below.
659  if (!ImmediateFitsAddrMode2Instruction(budget_arr_offset)) {
660  add(budget_array, budget_array, Operand{budget_arr_offset});
661  budget_arr_offset = 0;
662  }
663 
664  Register budget = temps.Acquire();
665  MemOperand budget_addr{budget_array, budget_arr_offset};
666  ldr(budget, budget_addr);
667  sub(budget, budget, Operand{budget_used}, SetCC);
668  str(budget, budget_addr);
669  }
670  b(ool_label, mi);
671 }
672 
673 Register LiftoffAssembler::LoadOldFramePointer() {
674  if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
675  return fp;
676  }
677  LiftoffRegister old_fp = GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kGpReg, {});
678  Label done, call_runtime;
679  ldr(old_fp.gp(), MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
680  cmp(old_fp.gp(),
681  Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
682  b(&call_runtime, eq);
683  mov(old_fp.gp(), fp);
684  jmp(&done);
685 
686  bind(&call_runtime);
687  LiftoffRegList regs_to_save = cache_state()->used_registers;
688  PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
689  MacroAssembler::Move(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address());
690  PrepareCallCFunction(1);
691  CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_load_old_fp(), 1);
692  if (old_fp.gp() != kReturnRegister0) {
693  mov(old_fp.gp(), kReturnRegister0);
694  }
695  PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
696 
697  bind(&done);
698  return old_fp.gp();
699 }
700 
701 void LiftoffAssembler::CheckStackShrink() {
702  {
703  UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
704  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
705  ldr(scratch, MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
706  cmp(scratch,
707  Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
708  }
709  Label done;
710  b(&done, ne);
711  LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
712  for (auto reg : kGpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
713  for (auto reg : kFpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
714  PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
715  MacroAssembler::Move(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address());
716  PrepareCallCFunction(1);
717  CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_shrink_stack(), 1);
718  // Restore old FP. We don't need to restore old SP explicitly, because
719  // it will be restored from FP in LeaveFrame before return.
720  mov(fp, kReturnRegister0);
721  PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
722  bind(&done);
723 }

725 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister reg, WasmValue value) {
726  switch (value.type().kind()) {
727  case kI32:
728  MacroAssembler::Move(reg.gp(), Operand(value.to_i32()));
729  break;
730  case kI64: {
731  int32_t low_word = value.to_i64();
732  int32_t high_word = value.to_i64() >> 32;
733  MacroAssembler::Move(reg.low_gp(), Operand(low_word));
734  MacroAssembler::Move(reg.high_gp(), Operand(high_word));
735  break;
736  }
737  case kF32:
738  vmov(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(reg.fp()), value.to_f32_boxed());
739  break;
740  case kF64: {
741  Register extra_scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {}).gp();
742  vmov(reg.fp(), base::Double(value.to_f64_boxed().get_bits()),
743  extra_scratch);
744  break;
745  }
746  default:
747  UNREACHABLE();
748  }
749 }

791 namespace liftoff {
792 #define __ lasm->
793 inline void LoadInternal(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, LiftoffRegister dst,
794  Register src_addr, Register offset_reg,
795  int32_t offset_imm, LoadType type,
796  uint32_t* protected_load_pc = nullptr,
797  bool needs_shift = false) {
798  unsigned shift_amount = needs_shift ? type.size_log_2() : 0;
799  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type.value_type() == kWasmI64, dst.is_gp_pair());
800  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
801  if (type.value() == LoadType::kF64Load ||
802  type.value() == LoadType::kF32Load ||
803  type.value() == LoadType::kS128Load) {
804  // Remove the DCHECK and implement scaled offsets for these types if needed.
805  // For now this path is never used.
806  DCHECK(!needs_shift);
807  Register actual_src_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
808  lasm, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
809  if (type.value() == LoadType::kF64Load) {
810  // Armv6 is not supported so Neon can be used to avoid alignment issues.
811  CpuFeatureScope scope(lasm, NEON);
812  __ vld1(Neon64, NeonListOperand(dst.fp()),
813  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
814  } else if (type.value() == LoadType::kF32Load) {
815  // TODO(arm): Use vld1 for f32 when implemented in simulator as used for
816  // f64. It supports unaligned access.
817  Register scratch =
818  (actual_src_addr == src_addr) ? temps.Acquire() : actual_src_addr;
819  __ ldr(scratch, MemOperand(actual_src_addr));
820  __ vmov(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()), scratch);
821  } else {
822  // Armv6 is not supported so Neon can be used to avoid alignment issues.
823  CpuFeatureScope scope(lasm, NEON);
824  __ vld1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp(), 2),
825  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
826  }
827  } else {
828  MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(lasm, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg,
829  offset_imm, shift_amount);
830  if (protected_load_pc) *protected_load_pc = __ pc_offset();
831  switch (type.value()) {
832  case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
833  __ ldrb(dst.gp(), src_op);
834  break;
835  case LoadType::kI64Load8U:
836  __ ldrb(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
837  __ mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0));
838  break;
839  case LoadType::kI32Load8S:
840  __ ldrsb(dst.gp(), src_op);
841  break;
842  case LoadType::kI64Load8S:
843  __ ldrsb(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
844  __ asr(dst.high_gp(), dst.low_gp(), Operand(31));
845  break;
846  case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
847  __ ldrh(dst.gp(), src_op);
848  break;
849  case LoadType::kI64Load16U:
850  __ ldrh(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
851  __ mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0));
852  break;
853  case LoadType::kI32Load16S:
854  __ ldrsh(dst.gp(), src_op);
855  break;
856  case LoadType::kI32Load:
857  __ ldr(dst.gp(), src_op);
858  break;
859  case LoadType::kI64Load16S:
860  __ ldrsh(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
861  __ asr(dst.high_gp(), dst.low_gp(), Operand(31));
862  break;
863  case LoadType::kI64Load32U:
864  __ ldr(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
865  __ mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0));
866  break;
867  case LoadType::kI64Load32S:
868  __ ldr(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
869  __ asr(dst.high_gp(), dst.low_gp(), Operand(31));
870  break;
871  case LoadType::kI64Load:
872  __ ldr(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
873  // GetMemOp may use a scratch register as the offset register, in which
874  // case, calling GetMemOp again will fail due to the assembler having
875  // ran out of scratch registers.
876  if (temps.CanAcquire()) {
877  src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(lasm, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg,
878  offset_imm + kSystemPointerSize);
879  } else {
880  __ add(src_op.rm(), src_op.rm(), Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
881  }
882  __ ldr(dst.high_gp(), src_op);
883  break;
884  default:
885  UNREACHABLE();
886  }
887  }
888 }
889 #undef __
890 } // namespace liftoff

927 void LiftoffAssembler::StoreTaggedPointer(Register dst_addr,
928  Register offset_reg,
929  int32_t offset_imm, Register src,
930  LiftoffRegList pinned,
931  uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
932  SkipWriteBarrier skip_write_barrier) {
933  static_assert(kTaggedSize == kInt32Size);
934  UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
935  Register actual_offset_reg = offset_reg;
936  if (offset_reg != no_reg && offset_imm != 0) {
937  if (cache_state()->is_used(LiftoffRegister(offset_reg))) {
938  // The code below only needs a scratch register if the {MemOperand} given
939  // to {str} has an offset outside the uint12 range. After doing the
940  // addition below we will not pass an immediate offset to {str} though, so
941  // we can use the scratch register here.
942  actual_offset_reg = temps.Acquire();
943  }
944  add(actual_offset_reg, offset_reg, Operand(offset_imm));
945  }
946  MemOperand dst_op = actual_offset_reg == no_reg
947  ? MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_imm)
948  : MemOperand(dst_addr, actual_offset_reg);
949 
950  if (protected_store_pc) *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
951 
952  str(src, dst_op);
953 
954  if (skip_write_barrier || v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
955 
956  // The write barrier.
957  Label exit;
958  CheckPageFlag(dst_addr, MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask,
959  kZero, &exit);
960  JumpIfSmi(src, &exit);
961  CheckPageFlag(src, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, eq, &exit);
962  CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(
963  dst_addr,
964  actual_offset_reg == no_reg ? Operand(offset_imm)
965  : Operand(actual_offset_reg),
966  SaveFPRegsMode::kSave, StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
967  bind(&exit);
968 }

970 void LiftoffAssembler::Load(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
971  Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
972  LoadType type, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
973  bool /* is_load_mem */, bool /* i64_offset */,
974  bool needs_shift) {
975  // Offsets >=2GB are statically OOB on 32-bit systems.
976  DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
977  liftoff::LoadInternal(this, dst, src_addr, offset_reg,
978  static_cast<int32_t>(offset_imm), type,
979  protected_load_pc, needs_shift);
980 }

982 void LiftoffAssembler::Store(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
983  uint32_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
984  StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
985  uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
986  bool /* is_store_mem */, bool /* i64_offset */) {
987  // Offsets >=2GB are statically OOB on 32-bit systems.
988  DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
989  UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
990  if (type.value() == StoreType::kF64Store) {
991  Register actual_dst_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
992  this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
993  // Armv6 is not supported so Neon can be used to avoid alignment issues.
994  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, NEON);
995  vst1(Neon64, NeonListOperand(src.fp()), NeonMemOperand(actual_dst_addr));
996  } else if (type.value() == StoreType::kS128Store) {
997  Register actual_dst_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
998  this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
999  // Armv6 is not supported so Neon can be used to avoid alignment issues.
1000  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, NEON);
1001  vst1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(src.low_fp(), 2),
1002  NeonMemOperand(actual_dst_addr));
1003  } else if (type.value() == StoreType::kF32Store) {
1004  // TODO(arm): Use vst1 for f32 when implemented in simulator as used for
1005  // f64. It supports unaligned access.
1006  Register actual_dst_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1007  this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1008  liftoff::CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters liftoff_temps{this, pinned};
1009  Register scratch =
1010  temps.CanAcquire() ? temps.Acquire() : liftoff_temps.Acquire();
1011  vmov(scratch, liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp()));
1012  str(scratch, MemOperand(actual_dst_addr));
1013  } else {
1014  MemOperand dst_op =
1015  liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1016  if (protected_store_pc) *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
1017  switch (type.value()) {
1018  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1019  src = src.low();
1020  [[fallthrough]];
1021  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1022  strb(src.gp(), dst_op);
1023  break;
1024  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1025  src = src.low();
1026  [[fallthrough]];
1027  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1028  strh(src.gp(), dst_op);
1029  break;
1030  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1031  src = src.low();
1032  [[fallthrough]];
1033  case StoreType::kI32Store:
1034  str(src.gp(), dst_op);
1035  break;
1036  case StoreType::kI64Store:
1037  str(src.low_gp(), dst_op);
1038  // GetMemOp may use a scratch register as the offset register, in which
1039  // case, calling GetMemOp again will fail due to the assembler having
1040  // ran out of scratch registers.
1041  if (temps.CanAcquire()) {
1042  dst_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg,
1043  offset_imm + kSystemPointerSize);
1044  } else {
1045  add(dst_op.rm(), dst_op.rm(), Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
1046  }
1047  str(src.high_gp(), dst_op);
1048  break;
1049  default:
1050  UNREACHABLE();
1051  }
1052  }
1053 }

1057 
1058 inline void AtomicOp32(
1059  LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
1060  uint32_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result,
1061  LiftoffRegList pinned,
1062  void (Assembler::*load)(Register, Register, Condition),
1063  void (Assembler::*store)(Register, Register, Register, Condition),
1064  void (*op)(LiftoffAssembler*, Register, Register, Register)) {
1065  Register store_result = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
1066 
1067  // Allocate an additional {temp} register to hold the result that should be
1068  // stored to memory. Note that {temp} and {store_result} are not allowed to be
1069  // the same register.
1070  Register temp = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
1071 
1072  // {LiftoffCompiler::AtomicBinop} ensures that {result} is unique.
1073  DCHECK(result.gp() != value.gp() && result.gp() != dst_addr &&
1074  result.gp() != offset_reg);
1075 
1076  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
1077  Register actual_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1078  lasm, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1079 
1080  __ dmb(ISH);
1081  Label retry;
1082  __ bind(&retry);
1083  (lasm->*load)(result.gp(), actual_addr, al);
1084  op(lasm, temp, result.gp(), value.gp());
1085  (lasm->*store)(store_result, temp, actual_addr, al);
1086  __ cmp(store_result, Operand(0));
1087  __ b(ne, &retry);
1088  __ dmb(ISH);
1089 }

1121 inline void AtomicBinop32(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Register dst_addr,
1122  Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
1123  LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result,
1124  StoreType type,
1125  void (*op)(LiftoffAssembler*, Register, Register,
1126  Register)) {
1127  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value, result};
1128  if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
1129  switch (type.value()) {
1130  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1131  __ LoadConstant(result.high(), WasmValue(0));
1132  result = result.low();
1133  value = value.low();
1134  [[fallthrough]];
1135  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1136  liftoff::AtomicOp32(lasm, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, value, result,
1137  pinned, &Assembler::ldrexb, &Assembler::strexb, op);
1138  return;
1139  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1140  __ LoadConstant(result.high(), WasmValue(0));
1141  result = result.low();
1142  value = value.low();
1143  [[fallthrough]];
1144  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1145  liftoff::AtomicOp32(lasm, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, value, result,
1146  pinned, &Assembler::ldrexh, &Assembler::strexh, op);
1147  return;
1148  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1149  __ LoadConstant(result.high(), WasmValue(0));
1150  result = result.low();
1151  value = value.low();
1152  [[fallthrough]];
1153  case StoreType::kI32Store:
1154  liftoff::AtomicOp32(lasm, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, value, result,
1155  pinned, &Assembler::ldrex, &Assembler::strex, op);
1156  return;
1157  default:
1158  UNREACHABLE();
1159  }
1160 }
1161 
1162 inline void AtomicOp64(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Register dst_addr,
1163  Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
1164  LiftoffRegister value,
1165  std::optional<LiftoffRegister> result,
1166  void (*op)(LiftoffAssembler*, LiftoffRegister,
1167  LiftoffRegister, LiftoffRegister)) {
1168  // strexd loads a 64 bit word into two registers. The first register needs
1169  // to have an even index, e.g. r8, the second register needs to be the one
1170  // with the next higher index, e.g. r9 if the first register is r8. In the
1171  // following code we use the fixed register pair r8/r9 to make the code here
1172  // simpler, even though other register pairs would also be possible.
1173  constexpr Register dst_low = r8;
1174  constexpr Register dst_high = r9;
1175 
1176  // Make sure {dst_low} and {dst_high} are not occupied by any other value.
1177  Register value_low = value.low_gp();
1178  Register value_high = value.high_gp();
1179  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_low, dst_high};
1180  auto regs_to_check = {&dst_addr, &offset_reg, &value_low, &value_high};
1181  auto re_pin = [regs_to_check, &pinned] {
1182  for (auto* reg : regs_to_check) {
1183  if (*reg != no_reg) pinned.set(*reg);
1184  }
1185  };
1186  re_pin();
1187  __ ClearRegister(dst_low, regs_to_check, pinned);
1188  re_pin();
1189  __ ClearRegister(dst_high, regs_to_check, pinned);
1190  re_pin();
1191 
1192  // Make sure that {result}, if it exists, also does not overlap with
1193  // {dst_low} and {dst_high}. We don't have to transfer the value stored in
1194  // {result}.
1195  Register result_low = no_reg;
1196  Register result_high = no_reg;
1197  if (result.has_value()) {
1198  result_low = result.value().low_gp();
1199  if (pinned.has(result_low)) {
1200  result_low = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1201  }
1202  pinned.set(result_low);
1203 
1204  result_high = result.value().high_gp();
1205  if (pinned.has(result_high)) {
1206  result_high = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1207  }
1208  pinned.set(result_high);
1209  }
1210 
1211  Register store_result = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1212 
1213  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
1214  Register actual_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1215  lasm, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1216 
1217  __ dmb(ISH);
1218  Label retry;
1219  __ bind(&retry);
1220  // {ldrexd} is needed here so that the {strexd} instruction below can
1221  // succeed. We don't need the value we are reading. We use {dst_low} and
1222  // {dst_high} as the destination registers because {ldrexd} has the same
1223  // restrictions on registers as {strexd}, see the comment above.
1224  __ ldrexd(dst_low, dst_high, actual_addr);
1225  if (result.has_value()) {
1226  __ mov(result_low, dst_low);
1227  __ mov(result_high, dst_high);
1228  }
1229  op(lasm, LiftoffRegister::ForPair(dst_low, dst_high),
1230  LiftoffRegister::ForPair(dst_low, dst_high),
1231  LiftoffRegister::ForPair(value_low, value_high));
1232  __ strexd(store_result, dst_low, dst_high, actual_addr);
1233  __ cmp(store_result, Operand(0));
1234  __ b(ne, &retry);
1235  __ dmb(ISH);
1236 
1237  if (result.has_value()) {
1238  if (result_low != result.value().low_gp()) {
1239  __ mov(result.value().low_gp(), result_low);
1240  }
1241  if (result_high != result.value().high_gp()) {
1242  __ mov(result.value().high_gp(), result_high);
1243  }
1244  }
1245 }
1246 
1247 inline void I64Store(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, LiftoffRegister dst,
1248  LiftoffRegister, LiftoffRegister src) {
1249  __ mov(dst.low_gp(), src.low_gp());
1250  __ mov(dst.high_gp(), src.high_gp());
1251 }
1252 
1253 #undef __
1254 } // namespace liftoff
1255 
1256 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicLoad(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
1257  Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
1258  LoadType type, LiftoffRegList /* pinned */,
1259  bool /* i64_offset */) {
1260  if (type.value() != LoadType::kI64Load) {
1261  Load(dst, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, type, nullptr, true);
1262  dmb(ISH);
1263  return;
1264  }
1265  // ldrexd loads a 64 bit word into two registers. The first register needs to
1266  // have an even index, e.g. r8, the second register needs to be the one with
1267  // the next higher index, e.g. r9 if the first register is r8. In the
1268  // following code we use the fixed register pair r8/r9 to make the code here
1269  // simpler, even though other register pairs would also be possible.
1270  constexpr Register dst_low = r8;
1271  constexpr Register dst_high = r9;
1272  SpillRegisters(dst_low, dst_high);
1273  {
1274  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1275  Register actual_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1276  this, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1277  ldrexd(dst_low, dst_high, actual_addr);
1278  dmb(ISH);
1279  }
1280 
1281  ParallelRegisterMove(
1282  {{dst, LiftoffRegister::ForPair(dst_low, dst_high), kI64}});
1283 }

1285 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicStore(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
1286  uint32_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
1287  StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
1288  bool /* i64_offset */) {
1289  if (type.value() == StoreType::kI64Store) {
1290  liftoff::AtomicOp64(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, src, {},
1291  liftoff::I64Store);
1292  return;
1293  }
1294 
1295  dmb(ISH);
1296  Store(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, src, type, pinned, nullptr, true);
1297  dmb(ISH);
1298  return;
1299 }

1388 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicExchangeTaggedPointer(
1389  Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
1390  LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
1391  liftoff::AtomicOp32(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, value, result,
1392  pinned, &Assembler::ldrex, &Assembler::strex,
1393  &liftoff::Exchange);
1394  if (v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
1395  // Emit the write barrier.
1396  Label exit;
1397  CheckPageFlag(dst_addr, MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask,
1398  kZero, &exit);
1399  JumpIfSmi(value.gp(), &exit);
1400  CheckPageFlag(value.gp(), MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, eq,
1401  &exit);
1402 
1403  UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
1404  Register actual_offset_reg = offset_reg;
1405  if (offset_reg != no_reg && offset_imm != 0) {
1406  if (cache_state()->is_used(LiftoffRegister(offset_reg))) {
1407  // The code below only needs a scratch register if the {MemOperand} given
1408  // to {str} has an offset outside the uint12 range. After doing the
1409  // addition below we will not pass an immediate offset to {str} though, so
1410  // we can use the scratch register here.
1411  actual_offset_reg = temps.Acquire();
1412  }
1413  add(actual_offset_reg, offset_reg, Operand(offset_imm));
1414  }
1415 
1416  CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(
1417  dst_addr,
1418  actual_offset_reg == no_reg ? Operand(offset_imm)
1419  : Operand(actual_offset_reg),
1420  SaveFPRegsMode::kSave, StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
1421  bind(&exit);
1422 }

1425 #define __ lasm->
1426 
1427 inline void AtomicI64CompareExchange(LiftoffAssembler* lasm,
1428  Register dst_addr_reg, Register offset_reg,
1429  uint32_t offset_imm,
1430  LiftoffRegister expected,
1431  LiftoffRegister new_value,
1432  LiftoffRegister result) {
1433  // To implement I64AtomicCompareExchange, we nearly need all registers, with
1434  // some registers having special constraints, e.g. like for {new_value} and
1435  // {result} the low-word register has to have an even register code, and the
1436  // high-word has to be in the next higher register. To avoid complicated
1437  // register allocation code here, we just assign fixed registers to all
1438  // values here, and then move all values into the correct register.
1439  Register dst_addr = r0;
1440  Register offset = r1;
1441  Register result_low = r4;
1442  Register result_high = r5;
1443  Register new_value_low = r2;
1444  Register new_value_high = r3;
1445  Register store_result = r6;
1446  Register expected_low = r8;
1447  Register expected_high = r9;
1448 
1449  // We spill all registers, so that we can re-assign them afterwards.
1450  __ SpillRegisters(dst_addr, offset, result_low, result_high, new_value_low,
1451  new_value_high, store_result, expected_low, expected_high);
1452 
1453  __ ParallelRegisterMove(
1454  {{LiftoffRegister::ForPair(new_value_low, new_value_high), new_value,
1455  kI64},
1456  {LiftoffRegister::ForPair(expected_low, expected_high), expected, kI64},
1457  {dst_addr, dst_addr_reg, kI32},
1458  {offset, offset_reg != no_reg ? offset_reg : offset, kI32}});
1459 
1460  {
1461  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
1462  [[maybe_unused]] Register temp = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1463  lasm, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg == no_reg ? no_reg : offset,
1464  offset_imm, dst_addr);
1465  // Make sure the actual address is stored in the right register.
1466  DCHECK_EQ(dst_addr, temp);
1467  }
1468 
1469  Label retry;
1470  Label done;
1471  __ dmb(ISH);
1472  __ bind(&retry);
1473  __ ldrexd(result_low, result_high, dst_addr);
1474  __ cmp(result_low, expected_low);
1475  __ b(ne, &done);
1476  __ cmp(result_high, expected_high);
1477  __ b(ne, &done);
1478  __ strexd(store_result, new_value_low, new_value_high, dst_addr);
1479  __ cmp(store_result, Operand(0));
1480  __ b(ne, &retry);
1481  __ dmb(ISH);
1482  __ bind(&done);
1483 
1484  __ ParallelRegisterMove(
1485  {{result, LiftoffRegister::ForPair(result_low, result_high), kI64}});
1486 }
1487 #undef __
1488 } // namespace liftoff
1489 
1490 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicCompareExchange(
1491  Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
1492  LiftoffRegister expected, LiftoffRegister new_value, LiftoffRegister result,
1493  StoreType type, bool /* i64_offset */) {
1494  if (type.value() == StoreType::kI64Store) {
1495  liftoff::AtomicI64CompareExchange(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm,
1496  expected, new_value, result);
1497  return;
1498  }
1499 
1500  // The other versions of CompareExchange can share code, but need special load
1501  // and store instructions.
1502  void (Assembler::*load)(Register, Register, Condition) = nullptr;
1503  void (Assembler::*store)(Register, Register, Register, Condition) = nullptr;
1504 
1505  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr};
1506  if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
1507  // We need to remember the high word of {result}, so we can set it to zero in
1508  // the end if necessary.
1509  Register result_high = no_reg;
1510  switch (type.value()) {
1511  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1512  result_high = result.high_gp();
1513  result = result.low();
1514  new_value = new_value.low();
1515  expected = expected.low();
1516  [[fallthrough]];
1517  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1518  load = &Assembler::ldrexb;
1519  store = &Assembler::strexb;
1520  // We have to clear the high bits of {expected}, as we can only do a
1521  // 32-bit comparison. If the {expected} register is used, we spill it
1522  // first.
1523  if (cache_state()->is_used(expected)) {
1524  SpillRegister(expected);
1525  }
1526  uxtb(expected.gp(), expected.gp());
1527  break;
1528  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1529  result_high = result.high_gp();
1530  result = result.low();
1531  new_value = new_value.low();
1532  expected = expected.low();
1533  [[fallthrough]];
1534  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1535  load = &Assembler::ldrexh;
1536  store = &Assembler::strexh;
1537  // We have to clear the high bits of {expected}, as we can only do a
1538  // 32-bit comparison. If the {expected} register is used, we spill it
1539  // first.
1540  if (cache_state()->is_used(expected)) {
1541  SpillRegister(expected);
1542  }
1543  uxth(expected.gp(), expected.gp());
1544  break;
1545  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1546  result_high = result.high_gp();
1547  result = result.low();
1548  new_value = new_value.low();
1549  expected = expected.low();
1550  [[fallthrough]];
1551  case StoreType::kI32Store:
1552  load = &Assembler::ldrex;
1553  store = &Assembler::strex;
1554  break;
1555  default:
1556  UNREACHABLE();
1557  }
1558  pinned.set(new_value);
1559  pinned.set(expected);
1560 
1561  Register result_reg = result.gp();
1562  if (pinned.has(result)) {
1563  result_reg = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1564  }
1565  pinned.set(LiftoffRegister(result));
1566  Register store_result = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1567 
1568  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1569  Register actual_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1570  this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1571 
1572  Label retry;
1573  Label done;
1574  dmb(ISH);
1575  bind(&retry);
1576  (this->*load)(result.gp(), actual_addr, al);
1577  cmp(result.gp(), expected.gp());
1578  b(ne, &done);
1579  (this->*store)(store_result, new_value.gp(), actual_addr, al);
1580  cmp(store_result, Operand(0));
1581  b(ne, &retry);
1582  dmb(ISH);
1583  bind(&done);
1584 
1585  if (result.gp() != result_reg) {
1586  mov(result.gp(), result_reg);
1587  }
1588  if (result_high != no_reg) {
1589  LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister(result_high), WasmValue(0));
1590  }
1591 }

1616 void LiftoffAssembler::MoveStackValue(uint32_t dst_offset, uint32_t src_offset,
1617  ValueKind kind) {
1618  DCHECK_NE(dst_offset, src_offset);
1619  liftoff::CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters temps{this};
1620  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1621  const int kRegSize = 4;
1622  DCHECK_EQ(0, SlotSizeForType(kind) % kRegSize);
1623  int words = SlotSizeForType(kind) / kRegSize;
1624  if (src_offset < dst_offset) {
1625  do {
1626  ldr(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src_offset));
1627  str(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(dst_offset));
1628  dst_offset -= kSystemPointerSize;
1629  src_offset -= kSystemPointerSize;
1630  } while (--words);
1631  } else {
1632  while (words--) {
1633  ldr(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src_offset - words * kRegSize));
1634  str(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(dst_offset - words * kRegSize));
1635  }
1636  }
1637 }

1640  DCHECK_NE(dst, src);
1641  DCHECK(kind == kI32 || is_reference(kind));
1642  MacroAssembler::Move(dst, src);
1643 }

1645 void LiftoffAssembler::Move(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister src,
1646  ValueKind kind) {
1647  DCHECK_NE(dst, src);
1648  if (kind == kF32) {
1649  vmov(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst), liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src));
1650  } else if (kind == kF64) {
1651  vmov(dst, src);
1652  } else {
1653  DCHECK_EQ(kS128, kind);
1654  vmov(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), liftoff::GetSimd128Register(src));
1655  }
1656 }
1657 
1658 void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, LiftoffRegister reg, ValueKind kind) {
1659  // The {str} instruction needs a temp register when the immediate in the
1660  // provided MemOperand does not fit into 12 bits. This happens for large stack
1661  // frames. This DCHECK checks that the temp register is available when needed.
1662  DCHECK(UseScratchRegisterScope{this}.CanAcquire());
1663  DCHECK_LT(0, offset);
1664  RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1665  MemOperand dst(fp, -offset);
1666  liftoff::Store(this, reg, dst, kind);
1667 }
1668 
1669 void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, WasmValue value) {
1670  RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1671  MemOperand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1672  UseScratchRegisterScope assembler_temps(this);
1673  liftoff::CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters liftoff_temps{this};
1674  Register src = no_reg;
1675  // The scratch register will be required by str if multiple instructions
1676  // are required to encode the offset, and so we cannot use it in that case.
1677  if (!ImmediateFitsAddrMode2Instruction(dst.offset())) {
1678  src = liftoff_temps.Acquire();
1679  } else {
1680  src = assembler_temps.Acquire();
1681  }
1682  switch (value.type().kind()) {
1683  case kI32:
1684  mov(src, Operand(value.to_i32()));
1685  str(src, dst);
1686  break;
1687  case kI64: {
1688  int32_t low_word = value.to_i64();
1689  mov(src, Operand(low_word));
1690  str(src, liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(offset, kLowWord));
1691  int32_t high_word = value.to_i64() >> 32;
1692  mov(src, Operand(high_word));
1693  str(src, liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(offset, kHighWord));
1694  break;
1695  }
1696  default:
1697  // We do not track f32 and f64 constants, hence they are unreachable.
1698  UNREACHABLE();
1699  }
1700 }

1709 
1710 void LiftoffAssembler::FillStackSlotsWithZero(int start, int size) {
1711  DCHECK_LT(0, size);
1712  DCHECK_EQ(0, size % 4);
1713  RecordUsedSpillOffset(start + size);
1714 
1715  // We need a zero reg. Always use r0 for that, and push it before to restore
1716  // its value afterwards.
1717  push(r0);
1718  mov(r0, Operand(0));
1719 
1720  if (size <= 36) {
1721  // Special straight-line code for up to 9 words. Generates one
1722  // instruction per word.
1723  for (int offset = 4; offset <= size; offset += 4) {
1724  str(r0, liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(start + offset, kLowWord));
1725  }
1726  } else {
1727  // General case for bigger counts (9 instructions).
1728  // Use r1 for start address (inclusive), r2 for end address (exclusive).
1729  push(r1);
1730  push(r2);
1731  sub(r1, fp, Operand(start + size));
1732  sub(r2, fp, Operand(start));
1733 
1734  Label loop;
1735  bind(&loop);
1736  str(r0, MemOperand(r1, /* offset */ kSystemPointerSize, PostIndex));
1737  cmp(r1, r2);
1738  b(&loop, ne);
1739 
1740  pop(r2);
1741  pop(r1);
1742  }
1743 
1744  pop(r0);
1745 }

1748  ValueKind /* kind */) {

1926 namespace liftoff {
1927 inline void GeneratePopCnt(Assembler* assm, Register dst, Register src,
1928  Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
1929  DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst, scratch1, scratch2));
1930  if (src == scratch1) std::swap(scratch1, scratch2);
1931  // x = x - ((x & (0x55555555 << 1)) >> 1)
1932  assm->and_(scratch1, src, Operand(0xaaaaaaaa));
1933  assm->sub(dst, src, Operand(scratch1, LSR, 1));
1934  // x = (x & 0x33333333) + ((x & (0x33333333 << 2)) >> 2)
1935  assm->mov(scratch1, Operand(0x33333333));
1936  assm->and_(scratch2, dst, Operand(scratch1, LSL, 2));
1937  assm->and_(scratch1, dst, scratch1);
1938  assm->add(dst, scratch1, Operand(scratch2, LSR, 2));
1939  // x = (x + (x >> 4)) & 0x0F0F0F0F
1940  assm->add(dst, dst, Operand(dst, LSR, 4));
1941  assm->and_(dst, dst, Operand(0x0f0f0f0f));
1942  // x = x + (x >> 8)
1943  assm->add(dst, dst, Operand(dst, LSR, 8));
1944  // x = x + (x >> 16)
1945  assm->add(dst, dst, Operand(dst, LSR, 16));
1946  // x = x & 0x3F
1947  assm->and_(dst, dst, Operand(0x3f));
1948 }
1949 } // namespace liftoff
1950 
1951 bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_popcnt(Register dst, Register src) {
1952  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst};
1953  Register scratch1 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
1954  Register scratch2 = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1955  liftoff::GeneratePopCnt(this, dst, src, scratch1, scratch2);
1956  return true;
1957 }
1958 
1959 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_divs(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1960  Label* trap_div_by_zero,
1961  Label* trap_div_unrepresentable) {
1962  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SUDIV)) {
1963  bailout(kMissingCPUFeature, "i32_divs");
1964  return;
1965  }
1966  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, SUDIV);
1967  // Issue division early so we can perform the trapping checks whilst it
1968  // completes.
1969  bool speculative_sdiv = dst != lhs && dst != rhs;
1970  if (speculative_sdiv) {
1971  sdiv(dst, lhs, rhs);
1972  }
1973  Label noTrap;
1974  // Check for division by zero.
1975  cmp(rhs, Operand(0));
1976  b(trap_div_by_zero, eq);
1977  // Check for kMinInt / -1. This is unrepresentable.
1978  cmp(rhs, Operand(-1));
1979  b(&noTrap, ne);
1980  cmp(lhs, Operand(kMinInt));
1981  b(trap_div_unrepresentable, eq);
1982  bind(&noTrap);
1983  if (!speculative_sdiv) {
1984  sdiv(dst, lhs, rhs);
1985  }
1986 }
1987 
1988 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_divu(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1989  Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1990  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SUDIV)) {
1991  bailout(kMissingCPUFeature, "i32_divu");
1992  return;
1993  }
1994  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, SUDIV);
1995  // Check for division by zero.
1996  cmp(rhs, Operand(0));
1997  b(trap_div_by_zero, eq);
1998  udiv(dst, lhs, rhs);
1999 }

2001 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_rems(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
2002  Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
2003  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SUDIV)) {
2004  // When this case is handled, a check for ARMv7 is required to use mls.
2005  // Mls support is implied with SUDIV support.
2006  bailout(kMissingCPUFeature, "i32_rems");
2007  return;
2008  }
2009  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, SUDIV);
2010  // No need to check kMinInt / -1 because the result is kMinInt and then
2011  // kMinInt * -1 -> kMinInt. In this case, the Msub result is therefore 0.
2012  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2013  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2014  sdiv(scratch, lhs, rhs);
2015  // Check for division by zero.
2016  cmp(rhs, Operand(0));
2017  b(trap_div_by_zero, eq);
2018  // Compute remainder.
2019  mls(dst, scratch, rhs, lhs);
2020 }

2022 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_remu(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
2023  Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
2024  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SUDIV)) {
2025  // When this case is handled, a check for ARMv7 is required to use mls.
2026  // Mls support is implied with SUDIV support.
2027  bailout(kMissingCPUFeature, "i32_remu");
2028  return;
2029  }
2030  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, SUDIV);
2031  // No need to check kMinInt / -1 because the result is kMinInt and then
2032  // kMinInt * -1 -> kMinInt. In this case, the Msub result is therefore 0.
2033  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2034  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2035  udiv(scratch, lhs, rhs);
2036  // Check for division by zero.
2037  cmp(rhs, Operand(0));
2038  b(trap_div_by_zero, eq);

2040  mls(dst, scratch, rhs, lhs);
2041 }

2058 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_mul(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2059  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2060  // Idea:
2061  // [ lhs_hi | lhs_lo ] * [ rhs_hi | rhs_lo ]
2062  // = [ lhs_hi * rhs_lo | ] (32 bit mul, shift 32)
2063  // + [ lhs_lo * rhs_hi | ] (32 bit mul, shift 32)
2064  // + [ lhs_lo * rhs_lo ] (32x32->64 mul, shift 0)
2065  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2066  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2067  // scratch = lhs_hi * rhs_lo
2068  mul(scratch, lhs.high_gp(), rhs.low_gp());
2069  // scratch += lhs_lo * rhs_hi
2070  mla(scratch, lhs.low_gp(), rhs.high_gp(), scratch);
2071  // TODO(arm): use umlal once implemented correctly in the simulator.
2072  // [dst_hi|dst_lo] = lhs_lo * rhs_lo
2073  umull(dst.low_gp(), dst.high_gp(), lhs.low_gp(), rhs.low_gp());
2074  // dst_hi += scratch
2075  add(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp(), scratch);
2076 }

2148 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_clz(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2149  // return high == 0 ? 32 + CLZ32(low) : CLZ32(high);
2150  Label done;
2151  Label high_is_zero;
2152  cmp(src.high_gp(), Operand(0));
2153  b(&high_is_zero, eq);
2154 
2155  clz(dst.low_gp(), src.high_gp());
2156  jmp(&done);
2157 
2158  bind(&high_is_zero);
2159  clz(dst.low_gp(), src.low_gp());
2160  add(dst.low_gp(), dst.low_gp(), Operand(32));
2161 
2162  bind(&done);
2163  mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0)); // High word of result is always 0.
2164 }
2165 
2166 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_ctz(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2167  // return low == 0 ? 32 + CTZ32(high) : CTZ32(low);
2168  // CTZ32(x) = CLZ(RBIT(x))
2169  Label done;
2170  Label low_is_zero;
2171  cmp(src.low_gp(), Operand(0));
2172  b(&low_is_zero, eq);
2173 
2174  rbit(dst.low_gp(), src.low_gp());
2175  clz(dst.low_gp(), dst.low_gp());
2176  jmp(&done);
2177 
2178  bind(&low_is_zero);
2179  rbit(dst.low_gp(), src.high_gp());
2180  clz(dst.low_gp(), dst.low_gp());
2181  add(dst.low_gp(), dst.low_gp(), Operand(32));
2182 
2183  bind(&done);
2184  mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0)); // High word of result is always 0.
2185 }
2186 
2187 bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_popcnt(LiftoffRegister dst,
2188  LiftoffRegister src) {
2189  // Produce partial popcnts in the two dst registers, making sure not to
2190  // overwrite the second src register before using it.
2191  Register src1 = src.high_gp() == dst.low_gp() ? src.high_gp() : src.low_gp();
2192  Register src2 = src.high_gp() == dst.low_gp() ? src.low_gp() : src.high_gp();
2193  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst, src2};
2194  Register scratch1 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
2195  Register scratch2 = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
2196  liftoff::GeneratePopCnt(this, dst.low_gp(), src1, scratch1, scratch2);
2197  liftoff::GeneratePopCnt(this, dst.high_gp(), src2, scratch1, scratch2);
2198  // Now add the two into the lower dst reg and clear the higher dst reg.
2199  add(dst.low_gp(), dst.low_gp(), dst.high_gp());
2200  mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0));
2201  return true;
2202 }
2203 
2204 void LiftoffAssembler::IncrementSmi(LiftoffRegister dst, int offset) {
2205  if (!is_int12(offset)) {
2206  // For large offsets, ldr/str will need a scratch register, but we need
2207  // the single available scratch register here. So fold the offset into the
2208  // base address.
2209  // Note: if we ever want to use this function for callers that don't want
2210  // {dst} to get clobbered, we could spill it to the stack and restore it
2211  // later.
2212  add(dst.gp(), dst.gp(), Operand(offset));
2213  offset = 0;
2214  }
2215  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2216  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2217  ldr(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
2218  add(scratch, scratch, Operand(Smi::FromInt(1)));
2219  str(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
2220 }

2320 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_copysign(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
2321  DoubleRegister rhs) {
2322  constexpr uint32_t kF32SignBit = uint32_t{1} << 31;
2323  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2324  Register scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {}).gp();
2325  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
2326  VmovLow(scratch, lhs);
2327  // Clear sign bit in {scratch}.
2328  bic(scratch, scratch, Operand(kF32SignBit));
2329  VmovLow(scratch2, rhs);
2330  // Isolate sign bit in {scratch2}.
2331  and_(scratch2, scratch2, Operand(kF32SignBit));
2332  // Combine {scratch2} into {scratch}.
2333  orr(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
2334  VmovLow(dst, scratch);
2335 }
2336 
2337 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_copysign(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
2338  DoubleRegister rhs) {
2339  constexpr uint32_t kF64SignBitHighWord = uint32_t{1} << 31;
2340  // On arm, we cannot hold the whole f64 value in a gp register, so we just
2341  // operate on the upper half (UH).
2342  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2343  Register scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {}).gp();
2344  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
2345  VmovHigh(scratch, lhs);
2346  // Clear sign bit in {scratch}.
2347  bic(scratch, scratch, Operand(kF64SignBitHighWord));
2348  VmovHigh(scratch2, rhs);
2349  // Isolate sign bit in {scratch2}.
2350  and_(scratch2, scratch2, Operand(kF64SignBitHighWord));
2351  // Combine {scratch2} into {scratch}.
2352  orr(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
2353  vmov(dst, lhs);
2354  VmovHigh(dst, scratch);
2355 }

2357 bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_type_conversion(WasmOpcode opcode,
2358  LiftoffRegister dst,
2359  LiftoffRegister src, Label* trap) {
2360  switch (opcode) {
2361  case kExprI32ConvertI64:
2362  MacroAssembler::Move(dst.gp(), src.low_gp());
2363  return true;
2364  case kExprI32SConvertF32: {
2365  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2366  SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2367  vcvt_s32_f32(
2368  scratch_f,
2369  liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp())); // f32 -> i32 round to zero.
2370  vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2371  // Check underflow and NaN.
2372  vmov(scratch_f, Float32(static_cast<float>(INT32_MIN)));
2373  VFPCompareAndSetFlags(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp()), scratch_f);
2374  b(trap, lt);
2375  // Check overflow.
2376  cmp(dst.gp(), Operand(-1));
2377  b(trap, vs);
2378  return true;
2379  }
2380  case kExprI32UConvertF32: {
2381  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2382  SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2383  vcvt_u32_f32(
2384  scratch_f,
2385  liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp())); // f32 -> i32 round to zero.
2386  vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2387  // Check underflow and NaN.
2388  vmov(scratch_f, Float32(-1.0f));
2389  VFPCompareAndSetFlags(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp()), scratch_f);
2390  b(trap, le);
2391  // Check overflow.
2392  cmp(dst.gp(), Operand(-1));
2393  b(trap, eq);
2394  return true;
2395  }
2396  case kExprI32SConvertF64: {
2397  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2398  SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2399  vcvt_s32_f64(scratch_f, src.fp()); // f64 -> i32 round to zero.
2400  vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2401  // Check underflow and NaN.
2402  DwVfpRegister scratch_d = temps.AcquireD();
2403  vmov(scratch_d, base::Double(static_cast<double>(INT32_MIN - 1.0)));
2404  VFPCompareAndSetFlags(src.fp(), scratch_d);
2405  b(trap, le);
2406  // Check overflow.
2407  vmov(scratch_d, base::Double(static_cast<double>(INT32_MAX + 1.0)));
2408  VFPCompareAndSetFlags(src.fp(), scratch_d);
2409  b(trap, ge);
2410  return true;
2411  }
2412  case kExprI32UConvertF64: {
2413  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2414  SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2415  vcvt_u32_f64(scratch_f, src.fp()); // f64 -> i32 round to zero.
2416  vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2417  // Check underflow and NaN.
2418  DwVfpRegister scratch_d = temps.AcquireD();
2419  vmov(scratch_d, base::Double(static_cast<double>(-1.0)));
2420  VFPCompareAndSetFlags(src.fp(), scratch_d);
2421  b(trap, le);
2422  // Check overflow.
2423  vmov(scratch_d, base::Double(static_cast<double>(UINT32_MAX + 1.0)));
2424  VFPCompareAndSetFlags(src.fp(), scratch_d);
2425  b(trap, ge);
2426  return true;
2427  }
2428  case kExprI32SConvertSatF32: {
2429  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2430  SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2431  vcvt_s32_f32(
2432  scratch_f,
2433  liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp())); // f32 -> i32 round to zero.
2434  vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2435  return true;
2436  }
2437  case kExprI32UConvertSatF32: {
2438  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2439  SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2440  vcvt_u32_f32(
2441  scratch_f,
2442  liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp())); // f32 -> u32 round to zero.
2443  vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2444  return true;
2445  }
2446  case kExprI32SConvertSatF64: {
2447  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2448  SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2449  vcvt_s32_f64(scratch_f, src.fp()); // f64 -> i32 round to zero.
2450  vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2451  return true;
2452  }
2453  case kExprI32UConvertSatF64: {
2454  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2455  SwVfpRegister scratch_f = temps.AcquireS();
2456  vcvt_u32_f64(scratch_f, src.fp()); // f64 -> u32 round to zero.
2457  vmov(dst.gp(), scratch_f);
2458  return true;
2459  }
2460  case kExprI32ReinterpretF32:
2461  vmov(dst.gp(), liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp()));
2462  return true;
2463  case kExprI64SConvertI32:
2464  if (dst.low_gp() != src.gp()) mov(dst.low_gp(), src.gp());
2465  mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(src.gp(), ASR, 31));
2466  return true;
2467  case kExprI64UConvertI32:
2468  if (dst.low_gp() != src.gp()) mov(dst.low_gp(), src.gp());
2469  mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(0));
2470  return true;
2471  case kExprI64ReinterpretF64:
2472  vmov(dst.low_gp(), dst.high_gp(), src.fp());
2473  return true;
2474  case kExprF32SConvertI32: {
2475  SwVfpRegister dst_float = liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp());
2476  vmov(dst_float, src.gp());
2477  vcvt_f32_s32(dst_float, dst_float);
2478  return true;
2479  }
2480  case kExprF32UConvertI32: {
2481  SwVfpRegister dst_float = liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp());
2482  vmov(dst_float, src.gp());
2483  vcvt_f32_u32(dst_float, dst_float);
2484  return true;
2485  }
2486  case kExprF32ConvertF64:
2487  vcvt_f32_f64(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()), src.fp());
2488  return true;
2489  case kExprF32ReinterpretI32:
2490  vmov(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()), src.gp());
2491  return true;
2492  case kExprF64SConvertI32: {
2493  vmov(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()), src.gp());
2494  vcvt_f64_s32(dst.fp(), liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()));
2495  return true;
2496  }
2497  case kExprF64UConvertI32: {
2498  vmov(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()), src.gp());
2499  vcvt_f64_u32(dst.fp(), liftoff::GetFloatRegister(dst.fp()));
2500  return true;
2501  }
2502  case kExprF64ConvertF32:
2503  vcvt_f64_f32(dst.fp(), liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.fp()));
2504  return true;
2505  case kExprF64ReinterpretI64:
2506  vmov(dst.fp(), src.low_gp(), src.high_gp());
2507  return true;
2508  case kExprF64SConvertI64:
2509  case kExprF64UConvertI64:
2510  case kExprI64SConvertF32:
2511  case kExprI64UConvertF32:
2512  case kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
2513  case kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
2514  case kExprF32SConvertI64:
2515  case kExprF32UConvertI64:
2516  case kExprI64SConvertF64:
2517  case kExprI64UConvertF64:
2518  case kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
2519  case kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
2520  // These cases can be handled by the C fallback function.
2521  return false;
2522  default:
2523  UNREACHABLE();
2524  }
2525 }

2597 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
2598  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2599  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2600  // For signed i64 comparisons, we still need to use unsigned comparison for
2601  // the low word (the only bit carrying signedness information is the MSB in
2602  // the high word).
2603  Condition unsigned_cond = liftoff::MakeUnsigned(cond);
2604  Label set_cond;
2605  Label cont;
2606  LiftoffRegister dest = LiftoffRegister(dst);
2607  bool speculative_move = !dest.overlaps(lhs) && !dest.overlaps(rhs);
2608  if (speculative_move) {
2609  mov(dst, Operand(0));
2610  }
2611  // Compare high word first. If it differs, use it for the set_cond. If it's
2612  // equal, compare the low word and use that for set_cond.
2613  cmp(lhs.high_gp(), rhs.high_gp());
2614  if (unsigned_cond == cond) {
2615  cmp(lhs.low_gp(), rhs.low_gp(), eq);
2616  if (!speculative_move) {
2617  mov(dst, Operand(0));
2618  }
2619  mov(dst, Operand(1), LeaveCC, cond);
2620  } else {
2621  // If the condition predicate for the low differs from that for the high
2622  // word, the conditional move instructions must be separated.
2623  b(ne, &set_cond);
2624  cmp(lhs.low_gp(), rhs.low_gp());
2625  if (!speculative_move) {
2626  mov(dst, Operand(0));
2627  }
2628  mov(dst, Operand(1), LeaveCC, unsigned_cond);
2629  b(&cont);
2630  bind(&set_cond);
2631  if (!speculative_move) {
2632  mov(dst, Operand(0));
2633  }
2634  mov(dst, Operand(1), LeaveCC, cond);
2635  bind(&cont);
2636  }
2637 }

2639 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
2640  DoubleRegister lhs,
2641  DoubleRegister rhs) {
2642  VFPCompareAndSetFlags(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(lhs),
2643  liftoff::GetFloatRegister(rhs));

2646  if (cond != ne) {
2647  // If V flag set, at least one of the arguments was a Nan -> false.
2648  mov(dst, Operand(0), LeaveCC, vs);
2649  }
2650 }

2679 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTransform(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
2680  Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
2681  LoadType type,
2682  LoadTransformationKind transform,
2683  uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
2684  bool i64_offset) {
2685  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2686  Register actual_src_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
2687  this, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
2688  *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2689  MachineType memtype = type.mem_type();
2690 
2691  if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend) {
2692  if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2693  vld1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2694  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2695  vmovl(NeonS8, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), dst.low_fp());
2696  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint8()) {
2697  vld1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2698  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2699  vmovl(NeonU8, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), dst.low_fp());
2700  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2701  vld1(Neon16, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2702  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2703  vmovl(NeonS16, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), dst.low_fp());
2704  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint16()) {
2705  vld1(Neon16, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2706  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2707  vmovl(NeonU16, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), dst.low_fp());
2708  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2709  vld1(Neon32, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2710  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2711  vmovl(NeonS32, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), dst.low_fp());
2712  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint32()) {
2713  vld1(Neon32, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2714  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2715  vmovl(NeonU32, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), dst.low_fp());
2716  }
2717  } else if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend) {
2718  Simd128Register dest = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
2719  if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2720  vmov(dest, 0);
2721  vld1s(Neon32, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()), 0,
2722  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2723  } else {
2724  DCHECK_EQ(MachineType::Int64(), memtype);
2725  vmov(dest.high(), 0);
2726  vld1(Neon64, NeonListOperand(dest.low()),
2727  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2728  }
2729  } else {
2730  DCHECK_EQ(LoadTransformationKind::kSplat, transform);
2731  if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2732  vld1r(Neon8, NeonListOperand(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst)),
2733  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2734  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2735  vld1r(Neon16, NeonListOperand(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst)),
2736  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2737  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2738  vld1r(Neon32, NeonListOperand(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst)),
2739  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2740  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int64()) {
2741  vld1(Neon32, NeonListOperand(dst.low_fp()),
2742  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2743  MacroAssembler::Move(dst.high_fp(), dst.low_fp());
2744  }
2745  }
2746 }
2747 
2748 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadLane(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src,
2749  Register addr, Register offset_reg,
2750  uintptr_t offset_imm, LoadType type,
2751  uint8_t laneidx, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
2752  bool /* i64_offset */) {
2753  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2754  Register actual_src_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
2755  this, &temps, addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
2756  MacroAssembler::Move(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst),
2757  liftoff::GetSimd128Register(src));
2758  *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2759  LoadStoreLaneParams load_params(type.mem_type().representation(), laneidx);
2760  NeonListOperand dst_op =
2761  NeonListOperand(load_params.low_op ? dst.low_fp() : dst.high_fp());
2762  MacroAssembler::LoadLane(load_params.sz, dst_op, load_params.laneidx,
2763  NeonMemOperand(actual_src_addr));
2764 }
2765 
2766 void LiftoffAssembler::StoreLane(Register dst, Register offset,
2767  uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
2768  StoreType type, uint8_t laneidx,
2769  uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
2770  bool /* i64_offset */) {
2771  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2772  Register actual_dst_addr =
2773  liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(this, &temps, dst, offset, offset_imm);
2774  *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
2775 
2776  LoadStoreLaneParams store_params(type.mem_rep(), laneidx);
2777  NeonListOperand src_op =
2778  NeonListOperand(store_params.low_op ? src.low_fp() : src.high_fp());
2779  MacroAssembler::StoreLane(store_params.sz, src_op, store_params.laneidx,
2780  NeonMemOperand(actual_dst_addr));
2781 }

2783 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_swizzle(LiftoffRegister dst,
2784  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2785  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2786  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2787 
2788  NeonListOperand table(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs));
2789  if (dst == lhs) {
2790  // dst will be overwritten, so keep the table somewhere else.
2791  QwNeonRegister tbl = temps.AcquireQ();
2792  MacroAssembler::Move(tbl, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs));
2793  table = NeonListOperand(tbl);
2794  }
2795 
2796  vtbl(dst.low_fp(), table, rhs.low_fp());
2797  vtbl(dst.high_fp(), table, rhs.high_fp());
2798 }

2971 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64x2_pmin(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2972  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2973  QwNeonRegister dest = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
2974  QwNeonRegister left = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs);
2975  QwNeonRegister right = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs);
2976 
2977  VFPCompareAndSetFlags(right.low(), left.low());
2978  if (dst != rhs) vmov(dest.low(), right.low(), mi);
2979  if (dst != lhs) vmov(dest.low(), left.low(), NegateCondition(mi));
2980  VFPCompareAndSetFlags(right.high(), left.high());
2981  if (dst != rhs) vmov(dest.high(), right.high(), mi);
2982  if (dst != lhs) vmov(dest.high(), left.high(), NegateCondition(mi));
2983 }

3186 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_pmin(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
3187  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3188  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3189 
3190  QwNeonRegister tmp = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
3191  if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
3192  tmp = temps.AcquireQ();
3193  }
3194 
3195  QwNeonRegister left = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs);
3196  QwNeonRegister right = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs);
3197  vcgt(tmp, left, right);
3198  vbsl(tmp, right, left);
3199 
3200  if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
3201  vmov(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), tmp);
3202  }
3203 }
3204 
3205 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_pmax(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
3206  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3207  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3208 
3209  QwNeonRegister tmp = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
3210  if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
3211  tmp = temps.AcquireQ();
3212  }
3213 
3214  QwNeonRegister left = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs);
3215  QwNeonRegister right = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs);
3216  vcgt(tmp, right, left);
3217  vbsl(tmp, right, left);
3218 
3219  if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
3220  vmov(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), tmp);
3221  }
3222 }
