3314 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64x2_mul(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
3315  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3316  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3317 
3318  QwNeonRegister dst_neon = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
3319  QwNeonRegister left = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs);
3320  QwNeonRegister right = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs);
3321 
3322  // These temporary registers will be modified. We can directly modify lhs and
3323  // rhs if they are not uesd, saving on temporaries.
3324  QwNeonRegister tmp1 = left;
3325  QwNeonRegister tmp2 = right;
3326 
3327  LiftoffRegList used_plus_dst =
3328  cache_state()->used_registers | LiftoffRegList{dst};
3329 
3330  if (used_plus_dst.has(lhs) && used_plus_dst.has(rhs)) {
3331  tmp1 = temps.AcquireQ();
3332  // We only have 1 scratch Q register, so acquire another ourselves.
3333  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst};
3334  LiftoffRegister unused_pair = GetUnusedRegister(kFpRegPair, pinned);
3335  tmp2 = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(unused_pair);
3336  } else if (used_plus_dst.has(lhs)) {
3337  tmp1 = temps.AcquireQ();
3338  } else if (used_plus_dst.has(rhs)) {
3339  tmp2 = temps.AcquireQ();
3340  }
3341 
3342  // Algorithm from code-generator-arm.cc, refer to comments there for details.
3343  if (tmp1 != left) {
3344  vmov(tmp1, left);
3345  }
3346  if (tmp2 != right) {
3347  vmov(tmp2, right);
3348  }
3349 
3350  vtrn(Neon32, tmp1.low(), tmp1.high());
3351  vtrn(Neon32, tmp2.low(), tmp2.high());
3352 
3353  vmull(NeonU32, dst_neon, tmp1.low(), tmp2.high());
3354  vmlal(NeonU32, dst_neon, tmp1.high(), tmp2.low());
3355  vshl(NeonU64, dst_neon, dst_neon, 32);
3356 
3357  vmlal(NeonU32, dst_neon, tmp1.low(), tmp2.low());
3358 }

3451 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32x4_bitmask(LiftoffRegister dst,
3452  LiftoffRegister src) {
3453  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3454  Simd128Register tmp = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(src);
3455  Simd128Register mask = temps.AcquireQ();
3456 
3457  if (cache_state()->is_used(src)) {
3458  // We only have 1 scratch Q register, so try and reuse src.
3459  LiftoffRegList pinned{src};
3460  LiftoffRegister unused_pair = GetUnusedRegister(kFpRegPair, pinned);
3461  mask = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(unused_pair);
3462  }
3463 
3464  vshr(NeonS32, tmp, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(src), 31);
3465  // Set i-th bit of each lane i. When AND with tmp, the lanes that
3466  // are signed will have i-th bit set, unsigned will be 0.
3467  vmov(mask.low(), base::Double((uint64_t)0x0000'0002'0000'0001));
3468  vmov(mask.high(), base::Double((uint64_t)0x0000'0008'0000'0004));
3469  vand(tmp, mask, tmp);
3470  vpadd(Neon32, tmp.low(), tmp.low(), tmp.high());
3471  vpadd(Neon32, tmp.low(), tmp.low(), kDoubleRegZero);
3472  VmovLow(dst.gp(), tmp.low());
3473 }

3636 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i16x8_bitmask(LiftoffRegister dst,
3637  LiftoffRegister src) {

3640  Simd128Register mask = temps.AcquireQ();
3641

3645  LiftoffRegister unused_pair = GetUnusedRegister(kFpRegPair, pinned);
3646  mask = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(unused_pair);
3647  }

3650  // Set i-th bit of each lane i. When AND with tmp, the lanes that

3847 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i16x8_dot_i8x16_i7x16_s(LiftoffRegister dst,
3848  LiftoffRegister lhs,
3849  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3850  QwNeonRegister dest = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
3851  QwNeonRegister left = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs);
3852  QwNeonRegister right = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs);
3853 
3854  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3855  Simd128Register scratch = temps.AcquireQ();
3856 
3857  vmull(NeonS8, scratch, left.low(), right.low());
3858  vpadd(Neon16, dest.low(), scratch.low(), scratch.high());
3859 
3860  vmull(NeonS8, scratch, left.high(), right.high());
3861  vpadd(Neon16, dest.high(), scratch.low(), scratch.high());
3862 }

3864 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32x4_dot_i8x16_i7x16_add_s(LiftoffRegister dst,
3865  LiftoffRegister lhs,
3866  LiftoffRegister rhs,
3867  LiftoffRegister acc) {
3868  DCHECK_NE(dst, acc);
3869  QwNeonRegister dest = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
3870  QwNeonRegister left = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs);
3871  QwNeonRegister right = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs);
3872  QwNeonRegister accu = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(acc);
3873 
3874  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3875  Simd128Register scratch = temps.AcquireQ();
3876 
3877  vmull(NeonS8, scratch, left.low(), right.low());
3878  vpadd(Neon16, dest.low(), scratch.low(), scratch.high());
3879 
3880  vmull(NeonS8, scratch, left.high(), right.high());
3881  vpadd(Neon16, dest.high(), scratch.low(), scratch.high());
3882 
3883  vpaddl(NeonS16, dest, dest);
3884  vadd(Neon32, dest, dest, accu);
3885 }
3886 
3887 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_shuffle(LiftoffRegister dst,
3888  LiftoffRegister lhs,
3889  LiftoffRegister rhs,
3890  const uint8_t shuffle[16],
3891  bool is_swizzle) {
3892  Simd128Register dest = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
3893  Simd128Register src1 = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(lhs);
3894  Simd128Register src2 = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(rhs);
3895  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3896  Simd128Register scratch = temps.AcquireQ();
3897  if ((src1 != src2) && src1.code() + 1 != src2.code()) {
3898  // vtbl requires the operands to be consecutive or the same.
3899  // If they are the same, we build a smaller list operand (table_size = 2).
3900  // If they are not the same, and not consecutive, we move the src1 and src2
3901  // to q14 and q15, which will be unused since they are not allocatable in
3902  // Liftoff. If the operands are the same, then we build a smaller list
3903  // operand below.
3904  static_assert(!kLiftoffAssemblerFpCacheRegs.has(d28),
3905  "This only works if q14-q15 (d28-d31) are not used.");
3906  static_assert(!kLiftoffAssemblerFpCacheRegs.has(d29),
3907  "This only works if q14-q15 (d28-d31) are not used.");
3908  static_assert(!kLiftoffAssemblerFpCacheRegs.has(d30),
3909  "This only works if q14-q15 (d28-d31) are not used.");
3910  static_assert(!kLiftoffAssemblerFpCacheRegs.has(d31),
3911  "This only works if q14-q15 (d28-d31) are not used.");
3912  vmov(q14, src1);
3913  src1 = q14;
3914  vmov(q15, src2);
3915  src2 = q15;
3916  }
3917 
3918  int table_size = src1 == src2 ? 2 : 4;
3919 
3920  int scratch_s_base = scratch.code() * 4;
3921  for (int j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
3922  uint32_t imm = 0;
3923  for (int i = 3; i >= 0; i--) {
3924  imm = (imm << 8) | shuffle[j * 4 + i];
3925  }
3926  DCHECK_EQ(0, imm & (table_size == 2 ? 0xF0F0F0F0 : 0xE0E0E0E0));
3927  // Ensure indices are in [0,15] if table_size is 2, or [0,31] if 4.
3928  vmov(SwVfpRegister::from_code(scratch_s_base + j), Float32::FromBits(imm));
3929  }
3930 
3931  DwVfpRegister table_base = src1.low();
3932  NeonListOperand table(table_base, table_size);
3933 
3934  if (dest != src1 && dest != src2) {
3935  vtbl(dest.low(), table, scratch.low());
3936  vtbl(dest.high(), table, scratch.high());
3937  } else {
3938  vtbl(scratch.low(), table, scratch.low());
3939  vtbl(scratch.high(), table, scratch.high());
3940  vmov(dest, scratch);
3941  }
3942 }
3943

3986 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_alltrue(LiftoffRegister dst,
3987  LiftoffRegister src) {
3988  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3989  DwVfpRegister scratch = temps.AcquireD();
3990  vpmin(NeonU8, scratch, src.low_fp(), src.high_fp());
3991  vpmin(NeonU8, scratch, scratch, scratch);
3992  vpmin(NeonU8, scratch, scratch, scratch);
3993  vpmin(NeonU8, scratch, scratch, scratch);
3994  ExtractLane(dst.gp(), scratch, NeonS8, 0);
3995  cmp(dst.gp(), Operand(0));
3996  mov(dst.gp(), Operand(1), LeaveCC, ne);
3997 }

3999 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_bitmask(LiftoffRegister dst,
4000  LiftoffRegister src) {
4001  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4002  Simd128Register tmp = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(src);
4003  Simd128Register mask = temps.AcquireQ();
4004 
4005  if (cache_state()->is_used(src)) {
4006  // We only have 1 scratch Q register, so try and reuse src.
4007  LiftoffRegList pinned{src};
4008  LiftoffRegister unused_pair = GetUnusedRegister(kFpRegPair, pinned);
4009  mask = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(unused_pair);
4010  }
4011 
4012  vshr(NeonS8, tmp, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(src), 7);
4013  // Set i-th bit of each lane i. When AND with tmp, the lanes that
4014  // are signed will have i-th bit set, unsigned will be 0.
4015  vmov(mask.low(), base::Double((uint64_t)0x8040'2010'0804'0201));
4016  vmov(mask.high(), base::Double((uint64_t)0x8040'2010'0804'0201));
4017  vand(tmp, mask, tmp);
4018  vext(mask, tmp, tmp, 8);
4019  vzip(Neon8, mask, tmp);
4020  vpadd(Neon16, tmp.low(), tmp.low(), tmp.high());
4021  vpadd(Neon16, tmp.low(), tmp.low(), tmp.low());
4022  vpadd(Neon16, tmp.low(), tmp.low(), tmp.low());
4023  vmov(NeonU16, dst.gp(), tmp.low(), 0);
4024 }

4504 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_qfma(LiftoffRegister dst,
4505  LiftoffRegister src1,
4506  LiftoffRegister src2,
4507  LiftoffRegister src3) {
4508  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4509  Simd128Register scratch =
4510  dst == src3 ? temps.AcquireQ() : liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst);
4511  vmul(scratch, liftoff::GetSimd128Register(src1),
4512  liftoff::GetSimd128Register(src2));
4513  vadd(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(dst), liftoff::GetSimd128Register(src3),
4514  scratch);
4515 }

4743 void LiftoffAssembler::PushRegisters(LiftoffRegList regs) {
4744  RegList core_regs = regs.GetGpList();
4745  if (!core_regs.is_empty()) {
4746  stm(db_w, sp, core_regs);
4747  }
4748  LiftoffRegList fp_regs = regs & kFpCacheRegList;
4749  while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
4750  LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
4751  DoubleRegister first = reg.fp();
4752  DoubleRegister last = first;
4753  fp_regs.clear(reg);
4754  while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
4755  LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
4756  int code = reg.fp().code();
4757  // vstm can not push more than 16 registers. We have to make sure the
4758  // condition is met.
4759  if ((code != last.code() + 1) || ((code - first.code() + 1) > 16)) break;
4760  last = reg.fp();
4761  fp_regs.clear(reg);
4762  }
4763  vstm(db_w, sp, first, last);
4764  }
4765 }
4766 
4767 void LiftoffAssembler::PopRegisters(LiftoffRegList regs) {
4768  LiftoffRegList fp_regs = regs & kFpCacheRegList;
4769  while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
4770  LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetLastRegSet();
4771  DoubleRegister last = reg.fp();
4772  DoubleRegister first = last;
4773  fp_regs.clear(reg);
4774  while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
4775  LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetLastRegSet();
4776  int code = reg.fp().code();
4777  if ((code != first.code() - 1) || ((last.code() - code + 1) > 16)) break;
4778  first = reg.fp();
4779  fp_regs.clear(reg);
4780  }
4781  vldm(ia_w, sp, first, last);
4782  }
4783  RegList core_regs = regs.GetGpList();
4784  if (!core_regs.is_empty()) {
4785  ldm(ia_w, sp, core_regs);
4786  }
4787 }

4789 void LiftoffAssembler::RecordSpillsInSafepoint(
4790  SafepointTableBuilder::Safepoint& safepoint, LiftoffRegList all_spills,
4791  LiftoffRegList ref_spills, int spill_offset) {
4792  LiftoffRegList fp_spills = all_spills & kFpCacheRegList;
4793  int spill_space_size = fp_spills.GetNumRegsSet() * kSimd128Size;
4794  LiftoffRegList gp_spills = all_spills & kGpCacheRegList;
4795  while (!gp_spills.is_empty()) {
4796  LiftoffRegister reg = gp_spills.GetLastRegSet();
4797  if (ref_spills.has(reg)) {
4798  safepoint.DefineTaggedStackSlot(spill_offset);
4799  }
4800  gp_spills.clear(reg);
4801  ++spill_offset;
4802  spill_space_size += kSystemPointerSize;
4803  }
4804  // Record the number of additional spill slots.
4805  RecordOolSpillSpaceSize(spill_space_size);
4806 }

4813 void LiftoffAssembler::CallCWithStackBuffer(
4814  const std::initializer_list<VarState> args, const LiftoffRegister* rets,
4815  ValueKind return_kind, ValueKind out_argument_kind, int stack_bytes,
4816  ExternalReference ext_ref) {
4817  // Arguments are passed by pushing them all to the stack and then passing
4818  // a pointer to them.
4819  DCHECK(IsAligned(stack_bytes, kSystemPointerSize));
4820  // Reserve space in the stack.
4821  AllocateStackSpace(stack_bytes);
4822 
4823  int arg_offset = 0;
4824  for (const VarState& arg : args) {
4825  MemOperand dst{sp, arg_offset};
4826  if (arg.is_reg()) {
4827  liftoff::Store(this, arg.reg(), dst, arg.kind());
4828  } else if (arg.is_const()) {
4829  DCHECK_EQ(kI32, arg.kind());
4830  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4831  Register src = temps.Acquire();
4832  mov(src, Operand(arg.i32_const()));
4833  str(src, dst);
4834  } else {
4835  // Stack to stack move.
4836  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4837  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4838  MemOperand src = liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset());
4839  int words = SlotSizeForType(arg.kind()) / kSystemPointerSize;
4840  do {
4841  ldr(scratch, src);
4842  str(scratch, dst);
4843  src.set_offset(src.offset() + kSystemPointerSize);
4844  dst.set_offset(dst.offset() + kSystemPointerSize);
4845  } while (--words > 0);
4846  }
4847  arg_offset += value_kind_size(arg.kind());
4848  }
4849  DCHECK_LE(arg_offset, stack_bytes);
4850 
4851  // Pass a pointer to the buffer with the arguments to the C function.
4852  mov(r0, sp);
4853 
4854  // Now call the C function.
4855  constexpr int kNumCCallArgs = 1;
4856  PrepareCallCFunction(kNumCCallArgs);
4857  CallCFunction(ext_ref, kNumCCallArgs);
4858 
4859  // Move return value to the right register.
4860  const LiftoffRegister* result_reg = rets;
4861  if (return_kind != kVoid) {
4862  constexpr Register kReturnReg = r0;
4863  if (kReturnReg != rets->gp()) {
4864  Move(*rets, LiftoffRegister(kReturnReg), return_kind);
4865  }
4866  result_reg++;
4867  }
4868 
4869  // Load potential output value from the buffer on the stack.
4870  if (out_argument_kind != kVoid) {
4871  liftoff::Load(this, *result_reg, MemOperand{sp}, out_argument_kind);
4872  }
4873  add(sp, sp, Operand(stack_bytes));
4874 }
4875 
4876 void LiftoffAssembler::CallC(const std::initializer_list<VarState> args,
4877  ExternalReference ext_ref) {
4878  // First, prepare the stack for the C call.
4879  int num_args = static_cast<int>(args.size());
4880  PrepareCallCFunction(num_args);
4881 
4882  // Then execute the parallel register move and also move values to parameter
4883  // stack slots.
4884  int reg_args = 0;
4885  int stack_args = 0;
4886  ParallelMove parallel_move{this};
4887  for (const VarState& arg : args) {
4888  if (needs_gp_reg_pair(arg.kind())) {
4889  // All i64 arguments (currently) fully fit in the register parameters.
4890  DCHECK_LE(reg_args + 2, arraysize(kCArgRegs));
4891  parallel_move.LoadIntoRegister(
4892  LiftoffRegister::ForPair(kCArgRegs[reg_args],
4893  kCArgRegs[reg_args + 1]),
4894  arg);
4895  reg_args += 2;
4896  continue;
4897  }
4898  if (reg_args < int{arraysize(kCArgRegs)}) {
4899  parallel_move.LoadIntoRegister(LiftoffRegister{kCArgRegs[reg_args]}, arg);
4900  ++reg_args;
4901  continue;
4902  }
4903  MemOperand dst{sp, stack_args * kSystemPointerSize};
4904  ++stack_args;
4905  if (arg.is_reg()) {
4906  liftoff::Store(this, arg.reg(), dst, arg.kind());
4907  continue;
4908  }
4909  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4910  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4911  if (arg.is_const()) {
4912  DCHECK_EQ(kI32, arg.kind());
4913  mov(scratch, Operand(arg.i32_const()));
4914  str(scratch, dst);
4915  } else {
4916  // Stack to stack move.
4917  MemOperand src = liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset());
4918  ldr(scratch, src);
4919  str(scratch, dst);
4920  }
4921  }
4922  parallel_move.Execute();
4923 
4924  // Now call the C function.
4925  CallCFunction(ext_ref, num_args);
4926 }

4966 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_store_nonzero_if_nan(Register dst,

4981 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_store_nonzero_if_nan(Register dst,
4982  LiftoffRegister src,
4983  Register tmp_gp,
4984  LiftoffRegister tmp_s128,
4985  ValueKind lane_kind) {
4986  QwNeonRegister src_q = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(src);
4987  QwNeonRegister tmp_q = liftoff::GetSimd128Register(tmp_s128);
4988  if (lane_kind == kF32) {
4989  vpadd(tmp_q.low(), src_q.low(), src_q.high());
4990  LowDwVfpRegister tmp_d =
4991  LowDwVfpRegister::from_code(tmp_s128.low_fp().code());
4992  vadd(tmp_d.low(), tmp_d.low(), tmp_d.high());
4993  } else {
4994  DCHECK_EQ(lane_kind, kF64);
4995  vadd(tmp_q.low(), src_q.low(), src_q.high());
4996  }
4997  emit_store_nonzero_if_nan(dst, tmp_q.low(), lane_kind);
4998 }

5004 void LiftoffStackSlots::Construct(int param_slots) {
5005  DCHECK_LT(0, slots_.size());
5006  SortInPushOrder();
5007  int last_stack_slot = param_slots;
5008  for (auto& slot : slots_) {
5009  const int stack_slot = slot.dst_slot_;
5010  int stack_decrement = (last_stack_slot - stack_slot) * kSystemPointerSize;
5011  DCHECK_LT(0, stack_decrement);
5012  last_stack_slot = stack_slot;
5013  const LiftoffAssembler::VarState& src = slot.src_;
5014  switch (src.loc()) {
5015  case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kStack: {
5016  switch (src.kind()) {
5017  // i32 and i64 can be treated as similar cases, i64 being previously
5018  // split into two i32 registers
5019  case kI32:
5020  case kI64:
5021  case kF32:
5022  case kRef:
5023  case kRefNull: {
5024  asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSystemPointerSize);
5025  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(asm_);
5026  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5027  asm_->ldr(scratch,
5028  liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(slot.src_offset_, slot.half_));
5029  asm_->Push(scratch);
5030  } break;
5031  case kF64: {
5032  asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kDoubleSize);
5033  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(asm_);
5034  DwVfpRegister scratch = temps.AcquireD();
5035  asm_->vldr(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_));
5036  asm_->vpush(scratch);
5037  } break;
5038  case kS128: {
5039  asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSimd128Size);
5040  MemOperand mem_op = liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_);
5041  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(asm_);
5042  Register addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
5043  asm_, &temps, mem_op.rn(), no_reg, mem_op.offset());
5044  QwNeonRegister scratch = temps.AcquireQ();
5045  asm_->vld1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(scratch), NeonMemOperand(addr));
5046  asm_->vpush(scratch);
5047  break;
5048  }
5049  default:
5050  UNREACHABLE();
5051  }
5052  break;
5053  }
5054  case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kRegister: {
5055  int pushed_bytes = SlotSizeInBytes(slot);
5056  asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - pushed_bytes);
5057  switch (src.kind()) {
5058  case kI64: {
5059  LiftoffRegister reg =
5060  slot.half_ == kLowWord ? src.reg().low() : src.reg().high();
5061  asm_->push(reg.gp());
5062  break;
5063  }
5064  case kI32:
5065  case kRef:
5066  case kRefNull:
5067  asm_->push(src.reg().gp());
5068  break;
5069  case kF32:
5070  asm_->vpush(liftoff::GetFloatRegister(src.reg().fp()));
5071  break;
5072  case kF64:
5073  asm_->vpush(src.reg().fp());
5074  break;
5075  case kS128:
5076  asm_->vpush(liftoff::GetSimd128Register(src.reg()));
5077  break;
5078  default:
5079  UNREACHABLE();
5080  }
5081  break;
5082  }
5083  case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kIntConst: {
5084  asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSystemPointerSize);
5085  DCHECK(src.kind() == kI32 || src.kind() == kI64);
5086  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(asm_);
5087  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5088  // The high word is the sign extension of the low word.
5089  asm_->mov(scratch,
5090  Operand(slot.half_ == kLowWord ? src.i32_const()
5091  : src.i32_const() >> 31));
5092  asm_->push(scratch);
5093  break;
5094  }
5095  }
5096  }
5097 }
